    "analysis": "From the metric-level anomaly scan we have: a persistent, window-long high-side anomaly on recommendationservice.socket (25 points from 21:38Z), several short spikes on emailservice.workload and currencyservice.workload, and multiple brief deviations on checkoutservice and productcatalogservice KPIs. Trace coverage is limited—previous trace aggregate shows trace features mainly for checkoutservice; no trace records were reported for recommendationservice or emailservice, so trace-based downstream localization may be limited. To decide the root cause we should (1) check logs for symptom confirmation (e.g., elevated error counts, socket errors, or drops in row_count/throughput) for the candidate services, and (2) confirm whether recommendationservice socket anomaly corresponds to elevated error logs or other resource anomalies that point to a failure reason (socket error vs. network latency vs. resource exhaustion). Therefore the next atomic step is to analyze log.csv: compute global thresholds (P95 and P5) per (cmdb_id, log_name) using the full series, then filter to the incident window and candidate services and detect anomalies (>=P95 or <=P5). Return compact aggregates to confirm which services show abnormal log behavior during the incident window.",
